<head>LIE</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>TELL AN UNTRUTH</item>
<item>TELL A LIE</item>
<item>FIB</item>
<item>DISSEMBLE</item>
<item>DISSIMULATE</item>
<item>MISINFORM</item>
<item>MISLEAD</item>
<item>TELL A WHITE LIE</item>
<item>PERJURE ONESELF</item>
<item>COMMIT PERJURY</item>
<item>PREVARICATE</item>
<item>INFORMAL LIE THROUGH ONE'S TEETH</item>
<item>STRETCH THE TRUTH</item>
<item>FORMAL FORSWEAR ONESELF</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">說謊</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">誕</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>SAY what one KNOWS to be NOT TRUE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The are no very current words for lying in pre-Buddhist Chinese. Dàn 誕 "lie" and huǎng 謊 "lie" are both rare.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>說謊 is the current modern word for lying.</p>
<p>打謊 (coll) is a colloquial word for lying.</p>
<p>撒謊 is a colloquial term for spreading lies.</p>
<p>扯謊 (lit) is a more literary way of referring to lying.</p>
<p>扯白 (dial) is a dialect word for telling a lie.</p>
<p>佯言 (lit) is a literary way of referring to dishonest talk.</p>
<p>瞎說 refers irresponsible untruthful loose talk rather than strategic lying.</p>
<p>說鬼話 is a colloquial idiom for telling wild lies.</p>
<p>說瞎話 is a colloquial idiom for talking loosely without any basis in fact.</p>
<p>食言 refers to going back on one's word rather than lying in the first place and the word is marginal in the group.</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
    </div>
